From b1f243c03f5da0dd6697ca99fdfeb53ef84d2484 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thom de Hoog <thomdehoog@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 00:30:37 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Add optional AI Assistant tab for natural-language control

A chat tab drives the microscope in natural language. A Pydantic AI agent turns
the Remote Control commands into tools and dispatches them through the same
Acceptor, so every action obeys the existing validation, movement limits, and
one-mutation gate. The feature is additive and idle until the operator sends a
message; it reuses the five Remote Control modules unchanged.

New modules:
  mesoSPIM_AiAssistent_Config.py  endpoint + timing
  mesoSPIM_AiAssistent.py         tools, completion wrapper, worker, lifecycle
  mesoSPIM_AiAssistent_GUI.py     the AI Assistant tab
  assistant_manual.md             thin preamble (get_manual is the full reference)

Integration hooks mirror Remote Control: Core gains one attribute and two
delegate slots; MainWindow imports, creates, and shuts down the tab. The
Assistant and a network transport are mutually exclusive. Requires pydantic-ai.
